But the building was not suitable for the museum, neither spatially nor technically - there were no walls for hanging art exhibits, no suitable climate.
Yet it was used until the new stand in Vienna was given to contemporary art.
Since 2001, the building has been empty and more and more dilapidated.
Now the pavilion has been reconstructed by the architect Adolf Krischanitz, now bearing the name "House of the 21st Century" and will be used in the future as the Museum of Contemporary Art.
Tuesday night, the Belvedere Museum, to which the palace belongs, will open its first exhibition - a happy occasion in every respect.
