Debt on projects
Social projects under programmes such as Habitat, Save Public Places and 3×1 for migrants are at risk of not being completed or of being delayed by lack of economic resources, said Miguel Ángel López Miranda.
The director of urban social development said that if construction work has progressed so far, the state government now risks not being able to provide the necessary supplies, which require funds of more than 11 million pesos for the three programs.
